• Full Track Data (data from magnetic strip, data chip)
• CAV2/CVC2/CVV2/CID (3 or 4 digit value)
• PIN/PIN Block (personal ID number)
• Live PANs aren't in UAT or DEV
 
There are servers that use Fortanix encryption, however, it is necessary to perform scans to demonstrate that this information, even if it is at rest or in transit, is not visible or accessible from any other system that does not have the keys. That is why I request read permission for the Imperva_DAS account to be able to run sensitive data scans on the servers that I list below to attach as evidence. This permission is required for 3 days while the scans are executed during non-productive hours so as not to generate any type of load or affect the performance of the servers.

Prod Servers

QA Serves

eu2qacardb2lb
